---
title: "transmit (Payment Abstraction V2)"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> q_check_role: check caller role
    q_check_role --> q_error_role: caller lacks PRICE_ADMIN_ROLE
    q_error_role --> [*]: revert "access denied"
    q_check_role --> q_decode: caller has PRICE_ADMIN_ROLE

    q_decode --> q_iter: decode price reports array
    q_iter --> q_validate_feed: for each (feedId, price, timestamp) in reports
    q_iter --> [*]: all reports processed

    q_validate_feed --> q_check_stale: lookup feedInfo by feedId
    q_check_stale --> q_iter: feedId not configured (skip)
    q_check_stale --> q_check_timestamp: feedId configured

    q_check_timestamp --> q_iter: timestamp older than existing price (skip)
    q_check_timestamp --> q_check_freshness: timestamp newer than existing

    q_check_freshness --> q_iter: timestamp exceeds staleness threshold
    q_check_freshness --> q_store: timestamp within staleness threshold

    q_store --> q_iter: store price and timestamp for feedId

    note right of q_store
        INV-024: only PRICE_ADMIN_ROLE (WorkflowRouter) can push prices
        INV-025: newer prices overwrite older ones (monotonic timestamp)
        INV-026: stale prices are rejected based on stalenessThreshold
        INV-027: contract falls back to Data Feeds if no fresh Streams price exists
    end note
